nd lack of evidence. As crises around the globe lead to reconsiderations of the place of capitalism, Beck’s excavation of this little-known strand of Hayek’s thought—and its failure—is timely and instructive.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aCapitalism. 0aFree enterprise. 0aHayek, Friedrich A. von-(Friedrich August),-1899-1992. 7aHISTORY / General.2bisacsh  aCharles Darwin.  aF. A. Hayek.  acapitalism.  acultural evolution.  aevolution.  afree market.  agroup selection.  aliberalism.  amorality.  aprogress.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2018z978311068858040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226556147423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226556147/original  a978-3-11-068858-0  University of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2018b2018  aGBV-deGruyter-alles